# Architecture Boundary Rule

- Keep reusable editor domain logic inside `packages/*`.
- Keep app wiring and deployment-specific integration inside `excalidraw-app/*`.
- If behavior affects both app and package consumers, prefer implementing in `packages/excalidraw` (or lower package layers).
- Respect dependency direction:
  - `common` -> `math` -> `element` -> `excalidraw` -> `excalidraw-app`
- Do not introduce reverse dependencies between these layers.
- Avoid deep cross-package internal imports; use public exports and entry points.

## How to verify

- Confirm new shared logic is not placed only in `excalidraw-app`.
- Confirm imports do not create lower-layer dependency on higher layers.
- Confirm cross-package imports use published entry points, not internal private files.
- Confirm architecture-impacting changes update relevant docs in `dev-docs/`.
